#### **Model Solution for Q-A (b) — 7 marks**

All seven parts are leaves with $q = 1$ each.

**Step 1 — Effective quantity factor**

$$
\begin{aligned}
\text{Factor} &= (1 + 0.05) \times 1.15 \\
&= 1.05 \times 1.15 \\
&= 1.2075
\end{aligned}
$$

For every $q = 1$ part: $Q_{\text{eff}} = \lceil 1.2075 \rceil = 2$.

**Step 2 — Leaf-level cost (with $Q_{\text{eff}} = 2$)**

| **Part** | **c (₹)** | $Q_{\text{eff}}$ | **Cost (₹)** |
| :--- | ---: | :---: | ---: |
| MQ-135 | 420 | 2 | 840 |
| PMS5003 | 1,800 | 2 | 3,600 |
| ESP32 | 350 | 2 | 700 |
| OLED | 280 | 2 | 560 |
| Fan | 150 | 2 | 300 |
| Li-Po 2000 mAh | 550 | 2 | 1,100 |
| TP4056 | 35 | 2 | 70 |

**Step 3 — Total rolled-up cost**

$$
\begin{aligned}
C_{\text{total}} &= 840 + 3600 + 700 + 560 + 300 + 1100 + 70 \\
&= \text{₹ } 7170
\end{aligned}
$$

**Step 4 — Landed cost with 18 % GST**

$$
\begin{aligned}
C_{\text{landed}} &= 7170 \times 1.18 = \text{₹ } 8460.60
