## 5.3 KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning / Pitfall Callout

> [!WARNING]
> **Top 5 places where KTU students LOSE MARKS in BOM questions:**
> 1. **Forgetting the recursive base case.** Writing `getRolledUpCost()` without checking `isLeaf()` causes infinite recursion. **Always add:** `if (isLeaf()) return unitCost * quantity;`
> 2. **Forgetting to mark `implements Serializable`.** Without it, `ObjectOutputStream.writeObject()` throws `NotSerializableException`. **Always implement `Serializable` on every class in the tree.**
> 3. **Mixing up `quantity` (per-parent) vs. `effectiveQuantity` (with safety stock).** Examiners specifically test this. Remember: $q$ is what the *design* says, $Q_{\text{eff}}$ is what *procurement* must order.
> 4. **Computing GST on selling price instead of rolled-up cost.** GST is always calculated on the **landed manufacturing cost**, not on the marked-up price.
> 5. **Forgetting to close file streams / PrintWriters.** Always use `try-with-resources` or explicit `close()` to avoid file-locking issues in the lab exam.

