## 5.4 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **High-Density Rapid-Revision Checklist (must memorize):**
> - ✅ BOM = hierarchical list of every part needed to build a product.
> - ✅ In Java, BOM = **Composite Design Pattern** with abstract `Component`, concrete `LeafPart`, concrete `Assembly`.
> - ✅ Cost roll-up: **recursively** sum `unitCost × quantity` from leaves to root.
> - ✅ Effective quantity formula: $Q_{\text{eff}} = \lceil q \times (1 + s) \times k \rceil$.
> - ✅ Landed cost: $C_{\text{landed}} = C_{\text{raw}} \times (1 + \text{GST\%})$.
> - ✅ Selling price: $C_{\text{sell}} = C_{\text{landed}} \times (1 + \text{Margin\%})$.
> - ✅ Typical IoT BOM shrinkage = **3–5 %**, safety stock = **10–25 %**, GST = **18 %**, margin = **20–30 %**.
> - ✅ BOM persistence: **Java Serialization** (`.ser`) for binary, **CSV** for Excel/Python consumption.
> - ✅ Critical lead time = `max` of all leaves' lead times.
> - ✅ Every class in the tree **must implement `Serializable`** to be saveable.
> - ✅ The **explode()** method flattens the multi-level tree to a list of leaves for shop-floor use.
> - ✅ Use **`java.util.List<Component>`** (interface) with **`ArrayList<Component>`** (implementation) for the `children` field — examiners explicitly test interface-based programming.
> - ✅ GUI visualization is done with `javax.swing.JTree` in the lab (Bonus marks).
> - ✅ Database persistence uses **JDBC** + `PreparedStatement` with `INSERT INTO bom (parent_pn, child_pn, qty) VALUES (?,?,?)`.
> - ✅ Phantom BOM (virtual sub-assembly) is a sub-assembly that is **never stocked** and is exploded immediately into its components during procurement.

